<Author>cmazhk
<Content>Find something else! The hotel is new and if there weren't so many problems it would be a decent lower priced modern hotel to stay at., especially if you are traveling solo. You have to put your luggage on the bed or floor because room is so tiny. You cannot open the window shade so you can never get natural light in the daytime. The hot water always turned freezing cold after 5 minutes in the shower. The noise is horrible from the hallway. You continuously hear other doors slamming and people talking constantly in the hallway. I agree with HongKong Connie- you definitely do not need an alarm clock to wake up in AM!Pillows suck. The pillows are actually like the pillows you get on an airplane sitting in coach! Bed not so comfortable. Location is OK near Little India (kind of a pain to the subway) but they have to work out a lot of kinks before I ever stay there again. Next time I go to Singapore on a budget I think I will stay at the Keong Saik Hotel in Chinatown which has a great location. 
